            "stanza_text": "My sweetest Lesbia, let us live and love,\nAnd though the sager sort our deeds reprove,\nLet us not weigh them. Heaven's great lamps do dive\nInto their west, and straight again revive,\nBut soon as once set is our little light,\nThen must we sleep one ever-during night."
        },
        {
            "stanza_number": 2,
            "stanza_type": "sestet",
            "lines": [
                {
                    "line_number": 7,
