            ],
            "stanza_text": "If all would lead their lives in love like me,\nThen bloody swords and armor should not be;\nNo drum nor trumpet peaceful sleeps should move,\nUnless alarm came from the camp of love.\nBut fools do live and waste their little light,\nAnd seek with pain their ever-during night."
        },
        {
            "stanza_number": 3,
            "stanza_type": "sestet",
            "lines": [
                {
                    "line_number": 13,
                    "line_text": "When timely death my life and fortune ends,",
